[commands]
check_ntp_time=$USER1$/check_ntp_time -H $HOSTADDRESS$ -w 60 -c 120

[name]
check_ntp_time

[info]
Checks the clock offset between the local host and a remote NTP server.
[why]
To keep track of server clocks.
[how]
Connects to an NTP server and and compares the NTP clock to the local clock. It lets you set thresholds on accepted offset.
[platforms]
Not platform dependent

[support]
4

[tags]
ntp, time
